message.content:
Rewrite the sessions panel in the clui Rust TUI to match a reference screenshot design.

**Repo:** `/Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/clui`
**Rust workspace:** `/Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/clui/rust/`
**Run first:** `source "$HOME/.cargo/env"`

## Reference design (from screenshot)

Each session is a **bordered tile card**:
```
╭──────────────────────────────────╮
│ bro check out plans in the re... │   ← truncated title, white text
│ 04/01 01:13                       │   ← date MM/DD HH:MM, dim gray
╰──────────────────────────────────╯
```
- Selected tile: cyan border + bold white title
- Non-selected: DarkGray border + Gray title + dark Gray date
- 1 blank line gap between tiles
- At bottom: `... 120 more below` (centered, DarkGray) when items exist below
- At bottom: `up/dn | Ctrl+D/B page | scroll | Enter` (hint line, DarkGray)
- No outer border on the sessions area itself (tiles fill the space)
- Small left padding inside each tile: 1 space

## Changes required

### 1. Update `rust/crates/app/src/state.rs`

Add these fields to `AppState`:
```rust
pub sessions_scroll: usize,
pub sessions_selected: usize,
pub sessions_panel_rect: ratatui::layout::Rect,
```

Initialize in `AppState::new()`:
```rust
sessions_scroll: 0,
sessions_selected: 0,
sessions_panel_rect: ratatui::layout::Rect::default(),
```

Also update `SessionEntry` — change `modified: String` to `modified_secs: u64`:
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct SessionEntry {
    pub title: String,
    pub path: String,
    pub modified_secs: u64,
}
```

### 2. Update `rust/crates/app/src/session_loader.rs`

Change the modified field to store u64 seconds. Replace the modified calculation with:
```rust
let modified_secs = jsonl_file
    .metadata()
    .ok()
    .and_then(|m| m.modified().ok())
    .and_then(|t| t.duration_since(std::time::UNIX_EPOCH).ok())
    .map(|d| d.as_secs())
    .unwrap_or(0);
sessions.push(SessionEntry { title, path: path_str, modified_secs });
```

Sort by: `sessions.sort_by(|a, b| b.modified_secs.cmp(&a.modified_secs));`

### 3. Add `chrono` to `rust/crates/app/Cargo.toml`

Read the file first. Add to `[dependencies]`:
```toml
chrono = { workspace = true }
```

### 4. Replace `rust/crates/app/src/ui/sessions.rs` entirely

```rust
use ratatui::{
    layout::{Alignment, Rect},
    style::{Color, Modifier, Style},
    text::{Line, Span},
    widgets::{Block, BorderType, Borders, Clear, Paragraph},
    Frame,
};
use crate::state::AppState;

/// Height of one tile (top border + title + date + bottom border)
const TILE_H: u16 = 4;
/// Gap between tiles
const TILE_GAP: u16 = 1;
/// Total rows consumed per session entry
const TILE_STRIDE: u16 = TILE_H + TILE_GAP;
/// Rows reserved at bottom for indicators + hint
const BOTTOM_RESERVE: u16 = 2;

pub fn render_sessions(f: &mut Frame, state: &mut AppState, area: Rect) {
    // Store area for mouse hit-testing
    state.sessions_panel_rect = area;

    let entries = &state.session_entries;
    let total = entries.len();

    // Usable height for tiles
    let usable = area.height.saturating_sub(BOTTOM_RESERVE);
    let visible_count = (usable / TILE_STRIDE) as usize;

    // Clamp scroll
    let max_scroll = if total > visible_count { total - visible_count } else { 0 };
    if state.sessions_scroll > max_scroll {
        state.sessions_scroll = max_scroll;
    }

    let scroll = state.sessions_scroll;
    let selected = state.sessions_selected;
    let end = (scroll + visible_count).min(total);

    // Render tiles
    for (rel_idx, entry) in entries[scroll..end].iter().enumerate() {
        let abs_idx = scroll + rel_idx;
        let y = area.y + (rel_idx as u16) * TILE_STRIDE;
        let tile_rect = Rect::new(area.x, y, area.width, TILE_H);

        let is_selected = abs_idx == selected;

        let (border_color, title_style, date_style) = if is_selected {
            (
                Color::Cyan,
                Style::default().fg(Color::White).add_modifier(Modifier::BOLD),
                Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray),
            )
        } else {
            (
                Color::DarkGray,
                Style::default().fg(Color::Gray),
                Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray),
            )
        };

        let block = Block::default()
            .borders(Borders::ALL)
            .border_type(BorderType::Rounded)
            .border_style(Style::default().fg(border_color));

        let inner = block.inner(tile_rect);

        // Truncate title to fit
        let max_w = inner.width.saturating_sub(1) as usize; // 1 for left padding
        let title = truncate(&entry.title, max_w);
        let date_str = format_ts(entry.modified_secs);

        let text = vec![
            Line::from(Span::styled(format!(" {}", title), title_style)),
            Line::from(Span::styled(format!(" {}", date_str), date_style)),
        ];

        f.render_widget(block, tile_rect);
        let para = Paragraph::new(text);
        f.render_widget(para, inner);
    }

    // Bottom indicators
    let bottom_y = area.y + area.height.saturating_sub(BOTTOM_RESERVE);

    // "... N more above/below"
    let above = scroll;
    let below = total.saturating_sub(end);
    let indicator = if below > 0 && above > 0 {
        format!("↑ {} above · {} below ↓", above, below)
    } else if below > 0 {
        format!("... {} more below", below)
    } else if above > 0 {
        format!("... {} more above", above)
    } else {
        String::new()
    };

    if !indicator.is_empty() {
        let ind_rect = Rect::new(area.x, bottom_y, area.width, 1);
        let ind_para = Paragraph::new(Line::from(Span::styled(
            indicator,
            Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray),
        )))
        .alignment(Alignment::Center);
        f.render_widget(ind_para, ind_rect);
    }

    // Hint bar
    let hint_rect = Rect::new(area.x, bottom_y + 1, area.width, 1);
    let hint = Paragraph::new(Line::from(vec![
        Span::styled("up/dn", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray)),
        Span::styled(" | ", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray).add_modifier(Modifier::DIM)),
        Span::styled("Ctrl+D/B page", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray)),
        Span::styled(" | ", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray).add_modifier(Modifier::DIM)),
        Span::styled("scroll", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray)),
        Span::styled(" | ", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray).add_modifier(Modifier::DIM)),
        Span::styled("Enter", Style::default().fg(Color::DarkGray)),
    ]))
    .alignment(Alignment::Center);
    f.render_widget(hint, hint_rect);
}

fn truncate(s: &str, max: usize) -> String {
    if max == 0 { return String::new(); }
    let chars: Vec<char> = s.chars().collect();
    if chars.len() <= max {
        s.to_string()
    } else if max > 3 {
        format!("{}...", chars[..max - 3].iter().collect::<String>())
    } else {
        chars[..max].iter().collect()
    }
}

fn format_ts(secs: u64) -> String {
    // Convert Unix timestamp to MM/DD HH:MM (local time approximation via chrono)
    use chrono::{DateTime, Local, TimeZone};
    match Local.timestamp_opt(secs as i64, 0) {
        chrono::LocalResult::Single(dt) => dt.format("%m/%d %H:%M").to_string(),
        _ => "??/?? ??:??".to_string(),
    }
}
```

### 5. Update `rust/crates/app/src/ui/sidebar_left.rs`

The `render_sessions` call currently passes `state` immutably but now needs `&mut AppState` because we store the panel rect. Update the match arm:

Read `sidebar_left.rs` first. Find this line:
```rust
LeftPanel::Sessions => super::sessions::render_sessions(f, state, content_area),
```

Change to (no change needed if `state` is already `&mut`).

Check: `render_left_sidebar` signature — if it takes `state: &AppState`, change to `state: &mut AppState`. Also update the call in `ui/mod.rs`.

### 6. Update `rust/crates/app/src/router.rs`

Add sessions navigation. In the main match block, add these arms:

```rust
// Sessions panel navigation
AppEvent::Key { code: KeyCode::Up, .. }
    if state.layout.left_panel == crate::state::LeftPanel::Sessions
    && !matches!(state.layout.focus, crate::state::Focus::Input) =>
{
    if state.sessions_selected > 0 {
        state.sessions_selected -= 1;
        // Scroll up if selected went above viewport
        if state.sessions_selected < state.sessions_scroll {
            state.sessions_scroll = state.sessions_selected;
        }
    }
}
AppEvent::Key { code: KeyCode::Down, .. }
    if state.layout.left_panel == crate::state::LeftPanel::Sessions
    && !matches!(state.layout.focus, crate::state::Focus::Input) =>
{
    let total = state.session_entries.len();
    if total > 0 && state.sessions_selected + 1 < total {
        state.sessions_selected += 1;
        // Scroll down if selected went below viewport
        // visible_count: compute from panel height (approximate as 10 if unknown)
        let panel_h = state.sessions_panel_rect.height;
        let visible = if panel_h > 2 { ((panel_h - 2) / 5) as usize } else { 3 };
        if state.sessions_selected >= state.sessions_scroll + visible {
            state.sessions_scroll = state.sessions_selected.saturating_sub(visible - 1);
        }
    }
}
AppEvent::Key { code: KeyCode::Char('d'), modifiers }
    if modifiers.contains(KeyModifiers::CONTROL)
    && state.layout.left_panel == crate::state::LeftPanel::Sessions
    && !matches!(state.layout.focus, crate::state::Focus::Input) =>
{
    let total = state.session_entries.len();
    let panel_h = state.sessions_panel_rect.height;
    let page = if panel_h > 2 { ((panel_h - 2) / 5) as usize } else { 3 };
    state.sessions_selected = (state.sessions_selected + page).min(total.saturating_sub(1));
    state.sessions_scroll = state.sessions_selected;
}
AppEvent::Key { code: KeyCode::Char('b'), modifiers }
    if modifiers.contains(KeyModifiers::CONTROL)
    && state.layout.left_panel == crate::state::LeftPanel::Sessions
    && !matches!(state.layout.focus, crate::state::Focus::Input) =>
{
    let panel_h = state.sessions_panel_rect.height;
    let page = if panel_h > 2 { ((panel_h - 2) / 5) as usize } else { 3 };
    state.sessions_selected = state.sessions_selected.saturating_sub(page);
    state.sessions_scroll = state.sessions_selected;
}
```

Also update the mouse ScrollUp/ScrollDown handler — add sessions panel scroll. Find the existing scroll handlers and add sessions support:

In the `MouseEventKind::ScrollUp` arm, add at the top:
```rust
// Sessions panel scroll
if state.layout.left_panel == crate::state::LeftPanel::Sessions
    && state.layout.left_visible
{
    state.sessions_scroll = state.sessions_scroll.saturating_sub(1);
    return;
}
```

Similarly for `ScrollDown`:
```rust
if state.layout.left_panel == crate::state::LeftPanel::Sessions
    && state.layout.left_visible
{
    let total = state.session_entries.len();
    let panel_h = state.sessions_panel_rect.height;
    let visible = if panel_h > 2 { ((panel_h - 2) / 5) as usize } else { 3 };
    let max_scroll = total.saturating_sub(visible);
    if state.sessions_scroll < max_scroll {
        state.sessions_scroll += 1;
    }
    return;
}
```

Also add mouse click on session tiles:
```rust
AppEvent::Mouse {
    kind: crossterm::event::MouseEventKind::Down(crossterm::event::MouseButton::Left),
    col,
    row,
    ..
} => {
    // Check if click is inside sessions panel
    let rect = state.sessions_panel_rect;
    if state.layout.left_panel == crate::state::LeftPanel::Sessions
        && state.layout.left_visible
        && col >= rect.x && col < rect.x + rect.width
        && row >= rect.y && row < rect.y + rect.height
    {
        // Which tile was clicked? Each tile is 5 rows (4 + 1 gap)
        let rel_row = row.saturating_sub(rect.y);
        let tile_idx = (rel_row / 5) as usize;
        let abs_idx = state.sessions_scroll + tile_idx;
        if abs_idx < state.session_entries.len() {
            state.sessions_selected = abs_idx;
        }
        return;
    }
    // ... existing mouse down logic follows
```

**Important**: The existing `MouseEventKind::Down` handler already exists. Don't duplicate it. Instead, INSERT the sessions click check at the TOP of the existing Down handler, before the border drag logic. Use `if ... { ...; return; }` so it short-circuits.

### 7. Update `sidebar_left.rs` and `ui/mod.rs` for `&mut AppState`

Read both files. If `render_left_sidebar` takes `&AppState`, change to `&mut AppState`. Same for `render_sessions`. Update the call chain in `ui/mod.rs` accordingly.

### 8. Build and test

```bash
cd /Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/clui/rust && source "$HOME/.cargo/env" && cargo build -p clui 2>&1
```

Fix all errors:
- `modified` field renamed to `modified_secs` — update all references
- `render_sessions` signature change — update callers
- `sessions_panel_rect` not Copy-able if Rect isn't in scope — use `ratatui::layout::Rect::default()`
- Chrono import: `use chrono::{Local, TimeZone};`

Run tests: `cargo test 2>&1`

Commit:
```bash
cd /Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/clui
git add rust/crates/app/src/
git commit -m "feat(ui): sessions panel with tile cards, scroll, keyboard nav, mouse click"
```

Report: DONE, DONE_WITH_CONCERNS, NEEDS_CONTEXT, or BLOCKED. Include test count and whether build succeeded.

